cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for solving linear inverse problems in image processing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves training a single deep neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The network acts as a proximal operator for an optimization algorithm, which involves iterative algorithms and optimization theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of wavelet sparsity prior, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the experiments involve tasks such as compressive sensing and pixel-wise inpainting, which are common in multimedia processing (cs.MM).
